    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-02-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-02-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="144"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/2–1952: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Portugal</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d144fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_PORTERIF1">Porter</persName> (<gloss target="#t_GTI1"
                            >GTI</gloss>) and signed for the Acting Secretary by Rountree.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-02-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 19, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>436. For <persName corresp="#p_DORSZEJ1">Dorsz</persName>. <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> Athens urges SEC and Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_LOVETTRA1">Lovett</persName> as well as <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRADLEYGAON1">Gen Bradley</persName> indicate to Grk Reps at
                    Lisbon our displeasure and anxiety at polit intervention <gloss target="#t_GAF1"
                        >GAF</gloss>.<note n="2" xml:id="d144fn2">This sentence is a paraphrase of
                        telegram 3792, Feb. 19, from Athens, not printed. (740.5/2–1952)</note> Dept
                    believes, if opportunity offers, that emphasizing our views at that level might
                    have salutary effect. <persName corresp="#p_SAKELLARIOUA1"
                        >Sakellariou</persName> who is prime mover in “purge” of <gloss
                        target="#t_GAF1">GAF</gloss>, will be member of Grk Del.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WEBBJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
